### ==================== PHASE 1: AUTH EMAILS ====================

### 1.1 WELCOME EMAIL - Triggered on user registration
### Email sent to: new user's email
### Template: welcome.hbs
### Includes: Welcome message, role info, login link
### @name register_welcome_test
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "welcometest_{{$timestamp}}@example.com",
  "password": "TestPass123!",
  "firstName": "Email",
  "lastName": "Tester",
  "phoneNumber": "+254700000099",
  "role": "tasker"
}


### 1.2 PASSWORD RESET EMAIL - Request OTP for password reset
### Email sent to: user's email
### Template: password-reset.hbs
### Includes: OTP code (expires in 4 minutes), expiry time, support link
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "welcometest9@example.com"
}


### 1.3 PASSWORD RESET SUCCESS - Confirmation after successful reset
### Email sent to: user's email
### Template: password-reset-success.hbs
### Includes: Confirmation message, reset date/time, security notice
### ⚠️ Use OTP from previous email (1.2) - valid for 4 minutes
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "welcometest9@example.com",
  "otp": "062150",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword456!"
}


### 1.4 LOGIN NOTIFICATION EMAIL - User logs in (optional security feature)
### Email sent to: user's email
### Template: login-notification.hbs
### Includes: Login time, IP address, location, device info
### Note: Configure in auth.service if needed
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "odhi@gmail.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}


